<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: Background of special elements</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Bert Bos" href="mailto:bert@w3.org" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-background/#special-backgrounds" />
  <meta name="flags" content="" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The ‘::first-line’ pseudo-element is like an inline-level element for the purposes of the background" />
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   html {background: white; color: black; line-height: 1.3}
   #test {background: lime}
   #test::first-line {background: white}
   body {width: 10.5em}
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <p>Test passes if there is some green (0.5em wide, to be precise) at
   the end of the line below:.</p>

  <p id="test"
  >&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;&#x2001;</p>

 </body>
</html>
